title: Oregon Geospatial Enterprise Office, Wildfires - Classified Forestland - Urban Interface (SB360), Oregon, 2004
name: Oregon Geospatial Enterprise Office, Wildfires - Classified Forestland - Urban Interface (SB360), Oregon, 2004
description:
Abstract:
    Geographic areas classified as Forestland Urban Interface by county classification committees under SB360, "Oregon's Forestland Urban Interface Fire Protection Act of 1997." Currently, Jackson and Dechutes counties have completed this classification process. 
Purpose:
    "Oregon's Forestland Urban Interface Fire Protection Act of 1997", ORS 477.015 - 477.061, provides a process for county classification committees to identify and classify areas that will place certain fire hazard mitigation obligations on landowners.
